Problem
Read problem statements in Mandarin Chinese and Bengali.
Given nn (nn is even), determine the number of black cells in an n \times nn×n chessboard.

Input Format
The only line of the input contains a single integer nn.

Output Format
Output the number of black cells in an n \times nn×n chessboard.

Constraints
2 \leq n \leq 1002≤n≤100
nn is even
Sample 1:
Input
Output
8
32
Explanation:
Chess_Board.svg
There are 3232 black cells and 3232 white cells in an 8 \times 88×8 chessboard. So the answer is 3232.

Soltuion

